'''Derek Charles Bonham''' (1943-2007), was a [[United Kingdom|British]] [[Business magnate|industrialist]] who became [[chairman]] of [[Imperial Tobacco]], [[Cadbury|Cadbury Schweppes]] and [[Marconi Communications|Marconi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ft.com/cms/s/0/c6875d58-5d25-11dc-8d22-0000779fd2ac.html#axzz30foBZGxl|title=Derek Bonham dies aged 64|work=Financial Times|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref>

==Biography==

Derek Bonham was born on 12 July 1943 in the village of [[Swanbourne]], [[Buckinghamshire]], and educated at [[Bedford School]].<ref>http://www.oxforddnb.com/view/articleHL/99061?docPos=8&anchor=match</ref>  He was [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] of [[Hanson plc|Hanson Group]] between 1992 and 1997, [[chairman]] of [[Imperial Tobacco]] between 1996 and 2007, [[chairman]] of [[Cadbury|Cadbury Schweppes]] between 2000 and 2003, and [[chairman]] of [[Marconi Communications|Marconi]] between 2001 and 2002.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/obituaries/derek-bonham-402783.html|title=Derek Bonham|work=The Independent|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref>

Bonham died in [[London]] on 3 September 2007, aged 64.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.telegraph.co.uk/news/obituaries/1563307/Derek-Bonham.html|title=Derek Bonham|date=17 September 2007|work=Telegraph.co.uk|accessdate=2 October 2014}}</ref>

